# Security Policy

## Allowed
- Run read-only SQL queries (SELECT, WITH/CTEs)
- Inspect database schema and sample data
- Save validated, reusable queries to disk

## Never Do
- Execute DDL or DML statements (DROP, DELETE, UPDATE, INSERT, ALTER, CREATE, TRUNCATE)
- Attempt to access tables or databases the user has not been granted access to
- Expose database credentials, connection strings, or sensitive data in responses
- Bypass SQL safety checks or LIMIT constraints
